Brazilian Stock Movers: BM&FBovespa, OGX, Paranapanema Increase

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-06-17T20:24:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/brazilian-stock-movers-bm-fbovespa-rises-copel-vale-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 0.3 percent to 61,059.98.  BM&FBovespa SA (BVMF3)  (BVMF3 BS) gained 4 percent to 10.90 reais.
The operator of  Latin America ’s biggest securities exchange will
buy back as many as 30 million of its shares from July 1 until
the end of the year, according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS) rose 3.8
percent to 14.29 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire Eike Batista said it’s receiving offers for stakes
in its Brazilian crude and natural-gas projects and expects a
sale this year.  Paranapanema SA (PMAM3 BS) gained 9.1 percent to 4.68
reais. The Brazilian copper smelter gained on speculation  Vale
SA (VALE3)  will make a new takeover offer, said  Pedro Galdi , an analyst
at Sao Paulo-based brokerage SLW Corretora. An official at
Paranapanema’s outside press agency didn’t immediately respond
to a phone message and e-mail seeking comment. A press official
at Vale, who asked not to be identified due to internal policy,
declined to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
